                <h3>2.1 How Do They Work</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Balance</li>
                    <p>By arranging objects on picture symmertrically or avergely, we can make the effect like regular and peaceful. Meanwhile, objects being arranged are not necessarily to be same.</p>
                    <li>Unbalnce</li>
                    <p>Contrarily, by arranging objects on picture unbalanced, we can make the effect like opposing and intence.</p>
                    <li>Framing</li>
                    <p>By adding a frame or a foreground like a frame, we can make focus on the main object or hide something we do not want to show.</p>
                    <li>Leaving spaces</li>
                    <p>Unlike other composition, we need to monis somthing besides of the main object to make the focus on it, also giving auidence imaginary space.</p>
                    <li>Golden section</li>
                    <p>Being the composition which akways appear on flowers, snails and coonch, this composition comes from natural can bring us effect like harmonious and comfortable.</p>
                    <li>Vanishing point</li>
                    <p>By gathering lines on one point, we can show the sense of space and 3D effect in our picture.</p>
                </ul>
